# Error Codes

Clients always receives **200 HTTP Status**, that means service works good and can handle your requests. Another HTTP Status Codes means that service not available, for example _500_ - for unhandled exception, _502_ if service not working and etc.

To get more information about request state, client will receive a **Code** field in response. **Code** field can store next values:

| **Code.** | **Message, description.** |
| --- | --- |
| 10 | Approved, means that request is successfully executed. |
| 20 | Internal Error, means that something goes wrong while executing request. |
| 21 | Bad Request, client miss something in request. |
| 22 | Data not found. |
